x": [786.9, 870.5, 803.5, 887.1]}, {"text": "21", "bbox": [887.5, 870.5, 904.2, 887.1]}, {"text": "Equity — International", "bbox": [195.8, 891.3, 350.4, 908.0]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [602.2, 891.3, 618.9, 908.0]}, {"text": "7", "bbox": [711.1, 891.3, 719.5, 908.0]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [786.9, 891.3, 803.5, 908.0]}, {"text": "7", "bbox": [895.8, 891.3, 904.2, 908.0]}, {"text": "Convertible securities", "bbox": [195.8, 912.1, 341.5, 928.8]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [602.2, 912.1, 618.9, 928.8]}, {"text": "3", "bbox": [711.1, 912.1, 719.5, 928.8]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [786.9, 912.1, 803.5, 928.8]}, {"text": "3", "bbox": [895.8, 912.1, 904.2, 928.8]}, {"text": "Short-term investments", "bbox": [195.8, 933.0, 351.6, 949.6]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [602.2, 933.0, 618.9, 949.6]}, {"text": "1", "bbox": [711.1, 933.0, 719.5, 949.6]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [786.9, 933.0, 803.5, 949.6]}, {"text": "1", "bbox": [895.8, 933.0, 904.2, 949.6]}, {"text": "Total net assets at fair value", "bbox": [195.8, 960.1, 381.9, 976.7]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [568.9, 960.1, 577.2, 976.7]}, {"text": "24", "bbox": [610.5, 960.1, 627.2, 976.7]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [661.2, 960.1, 669.5, 976.7]}, {"text": "32", "bbox": [702.8, 960.1, 719.5, 976.7]}, {"text": "—", "bbox": [786.9, 960.1, 803.5, 976.7]}, {"text": "$", "bbox": [845.8, 960.1, 854.2, 976.7]}, {"text": "56", "bbox": [887.5, 960.1, 904.2, 976.7]}, {"text": "The Medicare Prescription Drug, Improvement and Modernization Act of 2003 introduced a prescription drug", "bbox": [162.5, 1031.2, 1081.6, 1052.0]}, {"text": "benefit under Medicare and prescribes a federal subsidy to sponsors of retiree healthcare benefit plans that offer", "bbox": [162.5, 1056.2, 1095.9, 1077.0]}, {"text": "prescription drug coverage that is “actuarially equivalent” to the benefits under Medicare Part D. Based on our", "bbox": [162.5, 1081.2, 1085.9, 1102.0]}, {"text": "application of the relevant regulatory formula, we determined that the prescription drug coverage related to our", "bbox": [162.5, 1106.2, 1090.2, 1127.0]}, {"text": "retiree healthcare benefit plan is not actuarially equivalent to the Medicare benefit for the vast majority of", "bbox": [162.5, 1131.2, 1045.3, 1152.0]}, {"text": "retirees. For the years ended December 31, 2015, and December 31, 2014, we did not receive federal subsidies.", "bbox": [162.5, 1156.2, 1091.1, 1177.0]}, {"text": "Employee 401(k) Savings Plan", "bbox": [162.5, 1207.3, 431.8, 1228.1]}, {"text": "A substantial number of our employees are covered under a savings plan that is qualified under Section 401(k) of", "bbox": [162.5, 1258.9, 1108.4, 1279.7]}, {"text": "the Internal Revenue Code. The plan permits employees to contribute from 1% to 100% of eligible", "bbox": [162.5, 1283.9, 987.7, 1304.7]}, {"text": "compensation, with up to 6% being eligible for matching contributions. Commencing January 1, 2010, an", "bbox": [162.5, 1308.9, 1044.6, 1329.7]}, {"text": "automatic enrollment feature was added to the plan for all new employees. The initial default contribution", "bbox": [162.5, 1333.9, 1047.1, 1354.7]}, {"text": "percentage for employees is 2% and will increase by 1% at the beginning of each plan year until the default", "bbox": [162.5, 1358.9, 1060.3, 1379.7]}, {"text": "contribution is 10% for plan years on and after January 1, 2012. The plan also permits us to provide a", "bbox": [162.5, 1383.9, 1009.3, 1404.7]}, {"text": "discretionary annual profit sharing contribution. We accrued a 2% contribution for 2015 and made contributions", "bbox": [162.5, 1408.9, 1099.7, 1429.7]}, {"text": "of 2% for each of 2014 and 2013 on eligible compensation for employees eligible on the last business day of the", "bbox": [162.5, 1433.9, 1100.3, 1454.7]}, {"text": "206", "bbox": [621.9, 1484.1, 653.1, 1504.9]}]}